your life and look like the hero.

01:15:37.400 --> 01:15:38.969
Me!

01:15:39.869 --> 01:15:43.139
Can you believe it?
I mean, what are the odds, right?

01:15:43.872 --> 01:15:45.676
That's what I thought.

01:15:46.476 --> 01:15:49.125
But it turns out that Clarence...

01:15:49.225 --> 01:15:53.458
...knew who I was the entire time.

01:15:55.651 --> 01:15:59.482
What I can't figure out is why
he would want to fuck with me!

01:16:03.125 --> 01:16:07.612
But I think now's a pretty good time
for you to tell us, Clarence...

01:16:07.712 --> 01:16:09.533
...I think we're all ears.

01:16:12.034 --> 01:16:15.636
Well, it's exactly like you said.
She needed a hero.

01:16:17.439 --> 01:16:19.976
I've been going to that bar for years.

01:16:20.076 --> 01:16:23.594
I was there when you two were happily
married and I watched it go sour.

01:16:25.214 --> 01:16:27.651
You're a pretty shitty guy, Patrick.

01:16:27.951 --> 01:16:31.154
I knew you wouldn't pass up an opportunity
to make a little money off killing your wife...

01:16:31.254 --> 01:16:33.291
...and getting her grandmother's money.

01:16:34.491 --> 01:16:37.093
That is why you won't sign
the divorce papers, right?

01:16:37.193 --> 01:16:40.654
The inheritance? As long as you're
married, you still control half of it...

01:16:40.754 --> 01:16:43.414
...just as soon as you can find
a way to get a hold of it.

01:16:43.966 --> 01:16:46.469
See, I pay attention to the details.

01:16:46.569 --> 01:16:49.072
That's how I know what
an amazing woman Alex really is...

01:16:49.172 --> 01:16:52.408
...even if she was too hurt
from you to show it to anyone.

01:16:52.508 --> 01:16:56.579
When I told you I wanted
to be her hero, I meant it.

01:16:59.281 --> 01:17:02.099
So, it turns out you were
our real villain all along.

01:17:07.522 --> 01:17:11.950
That is incredibly beautiful, man.

01:17:14.062 --> 01:17:17.532
I mean, that was... it's poetic.

01:17:19.035 --> 01:17:22.305
Really tugged at every single one
of my little heart strings.

01:17:24.973 --> 01:17:27.994
This broke loser paid me to kidnap you...

01:17:28.094 --> 01:17:30.997
...put your life at risk, got you shot!

01:17:31.097 --> 01:17:35.117
Does that sound like prince
fucking charming to you, Alex?

01:17:36.702 --> 01:17:38.942
Does that seem like a hero to you?

01:17:41.390 --> 01:17:43.628
I got news for you, baby.

01:17:44.661 --> 01:17:46.926
I got news for you, too.

01:17:48.630 --> 01:17:50.633
I don't think the hero's gonna win this time.

01:17:54.767 --> 01:17:56.205
Fuck!

01:17:56.305 --> 01:17:59.409
Fuck! Shit! That hurt!

01:17:59.509 --> 01:18:01.544
Yeah, it does.

01:18:02.945 --> 01:18:05.381
It's getting very interesting tonight.

01:18:08.050 --> 01:18:10.899
I think it's time you take
a look inside that case.

01:18:27.202 --> 01:18:29.665
The combination is 1-4-3.

01:19:03.151 --> 01:19:06.108
Always be the smartest man
in the room, Patrick.

01:19:10.045 --> 01:19:13.917
The choice is yours. If you sign those
papers, you can walk out of here...

01:19:14.017 --> 01:19:17.822
...free to go on with your
pathetic excuse of a life. Or...

01:19:19.022 --> 01:19:22.057
...Alex can decide what to do
with you if you don't.

01:21:00.255 --> 01:21:02.182
I don't even know what to say.

01:21:04.226 --> 01:21:06.263
You don't have to say anything.

01:21:06.963 --> 01:21:08.965
I did what I came here to do.

01:21:13.752 --> 01:21:15.554
I wanted to help.

01:21:17.038 --> 01:21:18.595
Why?

01:21:19.403 --> 01:21:21.190
You don't even know me.

01:21:22.211 --> 01:21:24.414
Because I love you, Alex.

01:21:24.964 --> 01:21:27.384
I have from the first moment I saw you.

01:21:28.584 --> 01:21:32.603
Heck, I've been coming to your bar
every night for years, I don't even drink.

01:21:33.990 --> 01:21:35.846
I wanted to know you.

01:21:36.959 --> 01:21:38.844
I really wanted to know you.

01:21:40.262 --> 01:21:42.832
I saw what he was doing
to you and I hated it.

01:21:42.932 --> 01:21:45.385
For me, sure, but more for you.

01:21:46.351 --> 01:21:48.438
You deserve so much better.

01:21:49.138 --> 01:21:51.436
I saw it, you wouldn't give anyone the time
of day because you were too busy...

01:21:51.536 --> 01:21:54.377
...guarding yourself from ever
being hurt like that again.

01:21:54.477 --> 01:21:58.160
When you guard yourself from pain you're also
preventing yourself from ever being loved.

01:22:01.583 --> 01:22:04.853
So you almost killed me
to show me that I'm alive?

01:22:08.189 --> 01:22:10.426
Yeah, something like that.

01:22:12.661 --> 01:22:14.931
So what happens now?

01:22:15.031 --> 01:22:18.401
The way I see it,
I think we only have two options.

01:22:18.501 --> 01:22:20.903
Option one, you shoot me.

01:22:21.003 --> 01:22:23.746
I deserve it. I put your life in danger.

01:22:23.846 --> 01:22:27.977
I fed you to the lion that was
your husband or ex-husband now.

01:22:28.077 --> 01:22:30.747
That seems only right that since
I put your life in danger...

01:22:30.847 --> 01:22:34.283
...you have my permission
to let you do the same.

01:22:34.883 --> 01:22:39.458
Or option two. You let the police
arrest me and storm the house.

01:22:39.558 --> 01:22:42.659
I'll go quietly and plead guilty
to any charge they give me.

01:22:42.759 --> 01:22:45.024
Only you need to promise me something.

01:22:45.594 --> 01:22:47.630
I need you to promise me that from now on...

01:22:47.730 --> 01:22:49.999
...you're gonna live your life
with your head up...

01:22:50.099 --> 01:22:53.536
...and know that you deserve
happiness every single day.

01:22:53.636 --> 01:22:57.651
Because somewhere out there,
there's this really messed up boy...

01:22:57.751 --> 01:23:02.592
...who loves this beautiful,
beautiful broken girl...

01:23:04.112 --> 01:23:06.582
...who doesn't know
what she's missing out on.

01:23:24.666 --> 01:23:28.470
But both of those options
don't really seem that positive for you.

01:23:29.072 --> 01:23:32.169
I don't think I really deserve
anything positive at the moment.

01:23:32.892 --> 01:23:35.692
Now it seems like you're the one that's
shutting out the potential happiness...

01:23:35.792 --> 01:23:37.678
...in your life.

01:23:40.348 --> 01:23:42.456
What would option three be?

01:23:44.187 --> 01:23:46.142
Option three?

01:23:46.522 --> 01:23:48.035
Yeah.

01:23:49.159 --> 01:23:51.446
There's gotta be option three.

01:23:53.029 --> 01:23:56.679
Well, if there's an option three,
I guess it'd have to be...

